I've actually created a hardcopy Trade Skill encyclopedia for myself... lol<br>
<br>
and Reelin<br>
<br>
Baking:  Easiest, but pretty useless, though the food you make lasts longer and can bestow temporary buffs<br>
<br>
Tailoring: Easy, useful, and somewhat profitable once you can make Cured Silk and Leather Padding<br>
<br>
Blacksmithing: Expensive, but very useful, not very profitable because by the time you get Platemail, people who could afford it already have Magical Armor<br>
<br>
Jewelcraft: Expensive, difficult, but profitable at higher levels.  However only worth while for Enchanters, as you need to enchant the metals for the profitable jewelry, and to outsource takes time and money.<br>
<br>
Brewing: FUN, and helps build Alcohol Tolerance when you imbibe the finished product.<br>
<br>
Fletching: Useful for Rangers only<br>
<br>
Pottery: ? and thats a big capital ?<br>
<br>
Alchemy, Make Poison, and Tinkering: Class or Race specific (Shaman, Rogue, Gnome)<br>
<br>
<br>
Good Luck!<br>
<br>
