My little kitty bard had to learn pottery, and has now achieved mastery (122).  Eowenna is learning baking, because an extra point of wisdom *is* after all, an extra point of wisdom  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   and she keeps looting so many food items it seems silly not to put them to use.<br>
<br>
Legolia is fletching away, making increasingly better arrows.  By the way, fletching is a good back-up skill for any class that can use archery (Rogue included) because for under 50 skill you can make much better arrows than the blah, plain, short-range, low-damage ones NPC Vendors sell.  <br>
<br>
Also, if you pursue it you can make bows that hit harder or have lots less delay than NPC Vendors offer.  And several places on Luclin sell arrow components, but do *not* sell assembled arrows...  just some things to think about.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Galadri Leafshimmer ~ High Elf Paladin <BR>
